posts.title: Tax Math: Take $100, suppose it doubles each year for 10 years. You end up with $100,000. Now suppose if at the end of every year you tax it by 25%. After 10 years you have $26,000. A 25% tax has taken 75% of the value.

twitter.content:
The math on taxing wealth:

Take $100, suppose it doubles each year for ten years. 

You end up with ~$100,000

Now suppose if at the end of every year you tax it by 25%

After ten years you have $26,000

A 25% tax has taken 75% of the value.
